 Syntax (kovert) und Morphologie (overt) – ergibt, und unmittelbar mit der Präferenz für eines von zwei Mustern der Informationsstruktur zusammenhängt, die funktional äquivalent sind und eine Analogie zum Distributivgesetz der Mathematik aufweisen.  aHow does the Thai language manage textual structure without a system of articles, finite verb forms, or conjunctions, whereas in German, these are virtually indispensable? Using a theoretical approach and based on detailed textual analyses, this study describes two functionally equivalent patterns of information structure (covert and overt) that interact in a constitutive way with their respective sentence and text grammar coding systems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexGrammar, ComparativexThai. 0aGerman languagexStudy and teachingxThai speakers. 0aGerman languagexTense. 0aGerman languagexVerb. 0aIntercultural communication. 0aThai languagexGrammar, ComparativexGerman. 0aThai languagexTense. 0aThai languagexVerb. 4aFunktionale Grammatik. 4aKontrastive Linguistik. 4aTextlinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aFunctional Grammar.  aTextual Linguistics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103720520 cprintz978311034151540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034163840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110341638423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110341638/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGru